    <title>Re: City NPC's MUST be reverted back.</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=18644</link>
    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I'd vote for reverting the city guards back.&amp;nbsp; I have a feeling that this server is going to be pretty crowded, at least or the first few months, and we're going to need as many exp spots as possible available.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The original reasoning on making the guards unattractive targets was to make sure that they were available to newbie characters.&amp;nbsp; But for this server, there's going to be very few actual newbies to the game.&amp;nbsp; The majority of people being attracted to this server are people wishing to relive how EQ use to be, or to experience content that they missed.&amp;nbsp; Also there's most likely not going to be a tutorial, and it's a "specialty" server, so there's no real need to have extra hand holding here for newbie players.&amp;nbsp; This server is going to be a harsher environment than the average server (at least at the start) like the PvP servers were.&amp;nbsp; And that should be expected by everyone trying it out.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Also, from what I remember, I usually felt much safer when there were people camping the guards.&amp;nbsp; They usually offered more help than the guards.&amp;nbsp; And many times you'd find yourself with unasked for buffs and heals.&amp;nbsp; It was great.&amp;nbsp; In fact, it probably did more good for newbies than anything else because it immersed you in the social aspect of the game right from the start&amp;nbsp; -- you start interacting with actual players and can ask them for help, etc.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Occasionally there were cases when you'd run to the guards and they were killed, and the person there wasn't very friendly and wouldn't help you, and you'd end up having to run to the zone, and some times you'd end up dead because of it.&amp;nbsp; But those instances were few and far between.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;It was by far more of a boon the have higher lvl players hanging out hanging out there than not.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So particularly for this server, I see no reason whatsoever why the guards shouldn't be reverted back to their old state.&amp;nbsp; Some have stated in this thread that they thought they were easy money because they could be kited.&amp;nbsp; But this doesn't make much sense because what about hill giants?&amp;nbsp; Should we remove them too, because they actually have poorer MR than guards, and there's ever greater room in Rathe Mnts to kite them around.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;But if money from them is viewed as such a problem, go ahead and leave them without coins, but give them back their old resists, HP levels, and exp.&amp;nbsp; That way they wouldn't be quite as desirable.&amp;nbsp; People would mainly just use them if they needed an exp camp.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;But I'd say revert them back to the way they were, coinage and all.&amp;nbsp; They really didn't have anymore than the usual mob their lvl.&amp;nbsp; And low level players got a chance to loot FS weps and what-have-you.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I say revert them back, it can only help this server.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
