    <item>
      <title>City NPC's MUST be reverted back.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=16654#M16654</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;City NPC's and City Guards were a huge part of leveling back when there were only the original zones. Many people, including myself, spent a good majority of their time in cities/outside cities killing guards/npc's to level, be it solo, duo or even a full group. Not only was it fun to be doing something different than a dungeon, it was cool to chose a faction to destroy/raise and it totally immersified the feeling of the game. Being able to control whatever you attack/kill in original Everquest was what made it so great. Now alot of guards/npc's you can't even attack, and if you can, the experience is a fraction of what it used to be. It was nerfed a while back to make killing city npc/guards practically worthless. Some of them even dissapear on death with no corpse such as merchants do. There simply is not enough content in original for the sheer mass of interest this server has shown without the ability to kill city npc/guards like you used to. The reason players resorted to city npc/guards in the first place way back in original, was becuase many other places were full/camped and they could not get a group. This is going to happen all over again, except we won't have city guards/npc's anymore. It was a terrible decision to change city guard/npc's over and over throughout the years, to arrive at a point we are at now, where it is pointless to attack them. It completely ruins the immersion, and now it will do alot worse.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Certain things are understandable, such as the change that was made to city guards that are right outside the front of a city. They were buffed up and made extremely hard to kill. That is fine, we need those guards to protect lower levels. However inside &amp;amp; further outside cities is a different story. These guards/npc's need to be attackable and need to yield the same experience they used to, instead of 1/10th a light blue kill.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;An example are the Dwarf Citizens in Butcherblock Mountains. Extremely popular for druids back in the day. There are about 5 different camps of these citizens, and almost every class could be seen here and there camping them. Now, you cannot even attack them whatsoever.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Another example are the bards around freeport, some instantly dissapear upon death now and yield no experience, while others just give 1/10th a light blue kill.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Mechanics in Akanon.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Freeport guards.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ogre guards.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Barbarian guards.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Gnomes in steamfont/lesser fay.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Gnome guards in steamfont.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Etc. etc. These experience locations are all now ruined, and worthless. These spots and many more represent a huge fraction of the world that we are a part of. Removing these/making them useless is stupid. It not only ruins immersion but steals content away from us.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Revert all city/guard npc's save for the entrance guards back to the way they were before any changes happened!&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
