guides, or GM's in the game. The reason that camps worked is that other&#xD;
players respected each other enought to allow them to have an area or a&#xD;
mob to themselves. If another group or person moved into an area and&#xD;
started killing, there is really nothing that anyone can do about it&#xD;
except maybe yell in the zone that such and such is a camp stealer and&#xD;
hope that they get black listed.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Starting zones will honestly be the SUCK when the server goes live.&#xD;
Unless they are going to put infinite mobs to kill in the starting&#xD;
zones, grinding will be horrbile. The game is called everQUEST. If they&#xD;
put more quests in the game that yielded xp that did not always involve&#xD;
killing or if it did that mob was untouchable by anyone that is not on&#xD;
the quest, I believe that would help a LOT with the overcrowding of&#xD;
zones and areas. I understand that this may have not been the way the&#xD;
game was originally played but after 10 years they know for the&#xD;
millions of posts the things that DID NOT work well in with the&#xD;
original game and should hope to fix them so that if they had a chance&#xD;
to do it all agian, they would impliment those changes.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Trust me I am all for the nostalgia of starting the game that kept me&#xD;
up a many nights. What I do not want is to see the same exact problems&#xD;
that were around with the original game rehashed such as rangers being&#xD;
horrible tanks, and rogues having problems with losing agro and 1 point&#xD;
backstabs, pallies and sk's unable to hold agro and druids/wizards&#xD;
being the gods of soloing. I really think that the reason that WoW has&#xD;
been and continues to be so sucessful is that instances are the answer&#xD;
to dungeon overcrowding. Instead of camping the FBSS, make an instance&#xD;
where you have to&amp;nbsp; work through the dungeon to get to the mob that&#xD;
drops it and then defeat it.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I know that is not the ORIGINAL vision of the game&amp;nbsp; they keep&#xD;
telling us this will not be EQ CLASSIC. The fixed issues are supposedly&#xD;
staying fixed. So to me, it seems that it is counter-productive to put&#xD;
out a server and doing the same exact things that ended up causing the&#xD;
drop off the the subscriptions towards the release of the next gen&#xD;
games. Trust me the novelty will wear off quickly as people realize&#xD;
that they were just suckered into coming back into a world that really&#xD;
doesnt&amp;nbsp; offer anything more that what they had paid for and quit&#xD;
the game for in the first place.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
