      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;The only problem I have with killing guards is that if they do away with tutorial on this new server, you are going to have a lot of low levels running to the guards for help when they get an unexpected add or something they attack turns out to be more than they can handle. A lot of these players will suffer many needless deaths because the guards who are supposed to be there to protect them from being overwhelmed at an early age won't be there because someone came along and killed them for xp, loot, or whatever. Having specific, named guards there to be killed for quests, loot or xp, is good, but killing every generic guard that comes wandering by isn't, because you may be frustrating a true noob to the game who may then quit because he got killed 10 times in a row because there was no guard to save him. The game needs new players to survive, so they need a certain amount of sheltering through the early levels and this holds particularly true on a new server where there is no uber gear trickling down yet so they can't build themselves up without help from anyone.</description>
